arctgz(7)						   Miscellaneous Information Manual						    arctgz(7)

NAME
       arctgz - safety-first project lifecycle library for the arctgz archive format

SYNOPSIS
       use arctgz::{
	   init, load_config, save_config, compile, extract,
	   verify,
	   load_recipe, extract_recipe, execute_recipe,
	   ArctgzConfig, ArctgzManifest, FileEntry,
	   ArctgzRecipe, RecipeStep, Compression, ArctgzError
       };
       use std::path::Path;

       fn init(project_path: &Path, force: bool) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn load_config(project_path: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzConfig, ArctgzError>;
       fn save_config(project_path: &Path, config: &ArctgzConfig) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn compile(
	   project_path: &Path,
	   output_dir: Option<&Path>,
	   force: bool
       ) -> Result<PathBuf, ArctgzError>;
       fn extract(
	   archive_path: &Path,
	   output_dir: &Path,
	   force: bool
       ) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn verify(archive_path: &Path) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn load_recipe(project_path: &Path) -> Result<Option<ArctgzRecipe>, ArctgzError>;
       fn extract_recipe(archive_path: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzRecipe, ArctgzError>;
       fn execute_recipe(
	   output_dir: &Path,
	   recipe: &ArctgzRecipe,
	   force: bool
       ) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;

       struct ArctgzConfig {
	   pub name:	    String,
	   pub version:	    String,
	   pub include:	    Vec<String>,
	   pub compression: Compression,
       }

       struct ArctgzManifest {
	   pub name:	    String,
	   pub version:	    String,
	   pub created:	    DateTime<Utc>,
	   pub compression: Compression,
	   pub files:	    BTreeMap<String, FileEntry>,
       }

       struct FileEntry {
	   pub size:   u64,
	   pub sha512: String,
       }

       struct ArctgzRecipe {
	   pub name:	String,
	   pub version: String,
	   pub steps:	Vec<RecipeStep>,
       }

       enum RecipeStep {
	   Copy	  { from: String, to: String },
	   MkDir  { path: String },
	   Chmod  { path: String, mode: String },
	   Remove { path: String },
       }

       enum Compression {
	   Gzip,
	   Zstd,
       }

       enum ArctgzError { ... }

DESCRIPTION
       The  arctgz  library  provides a safe, cross-platform API for the full lifecycle of an arctgz project: scaffolding, configuration, compilation
       into a compressed and integrity-verified archive, verified extraction, standalone integrity verification, and  post-extraction  recipe  execu‐
       tion.

       All  operations	enforce	 strict path confinement, validate metadata before touching the filesystem, and use atomic file operations to prevent
       corruption and TOCTOU (time-of-check to time-of-use) races.

       The core functionality includes:

       • init() – scaffold a new project directory with a default configuration and an empty resource folder.

       • load_config() / save_config() – read and write validated project configuration.

       • compile() – create a compressed archive (gzip or zstd) with SHA-512 hashes and a manifest; supports parallel hashing via rayon.

       • extract() – unpack an archive with full integrity checks and path traversal prevention.

       • verify() – check archive integrity without writing files.

       • load_recipe() / extract_recipe() / execute_recipe() – manage and execute post-extraction recipes (copy, mkdir, chmod, remove).

       All paths are resolved with std::fs::canonicalize() (equivalent to realpath(3)), so symbolic links are followed during the home-directory con‐
       finement check.	The library is fully tested on Linux, macOS, and Windows.

INSTALLATION
       This man page can be installed system-wide using the provided installer script:

       curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash

       The script places arctgz.7 into /usr/local/share/man/man7/ and updates the man database.	 To uninstall, run:

       curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash -s -- uninstall

FUNCTIONS
       init(project_path, force)
	      Initialises a new arctgz project at project_path.	 Creates the directory, an include/ subdirectory, and  a  default  arctgz.init	file.
	      The default configuration includes "compression": "gzip".	 See ArctgzConfig for details.

       Security checks are performed before any filesystem changes; a failed call leaves no side effects.

       load_config(project_path)
	      Reads and validates arctgz.init.

       save_config(project_path, config)
	      Atomically writes a validated ArctgzConfig back to disk (temp file + rename).

       compile(project_path, output_dir, force)
	      Compiles the project into an .artgz archive.

       Steps:

       • Loads configuration via load_config().

       • Collects arctgz.init, the include/ files, and an optional recipe.json (validated automatically).

       • Computes SHA-512 hashes for every file in parallel using rayon.

       • Embeds an ArctgzManifest as manifest.json.

       • Compresses the tar stream with the configured algorithm (Compression::Gzip or Compression::Zstd).

       • Writes the archive atomically via a temporary file.

       Symlinks are rejected.  If a recipe.json is present, it is validated and included; invalid recipes cause RecipeInvalid.

       extract(archive_path, output_dir, force)
	      Extracts	an  archive with full verification.  Compression is detected automatically (gzip/zstd magic bytes).  All files are hashed and
	      checked against the manifest; any mismatch aborts with ChecksumMismatch.	Path traversal (absolute paths or ..) is rejected.   Existing
	      files are overwritten only when force is true.

       verify(archive_path)
	      Standalone  integrity check. Reads the archive, validates every file's hash and size against the manifest, ensures all manifest entries
	      are present, and checks for unsafe paths.	 No files are written.

       load_recipe(project_path)
	      Loads and validates recipe.json from a project directory. Returns Ok(None) if the file is absent.

       extract_recipe(archive_path)
	      Extracts and validates the embedded recipe.json from an archive. Returns RecipeNotFound if missing.

       execute_recipe(output_dir, recipe, force)
	      Runs the steps of a recipe inside output_dir.  Supported steps:

	      Copy { from, to }
		     Copy a file or directory.

	      MkDir { path }
		     Create a directory.

	      Chmod { path, mode }
		     Set Unix permissions (octal string).  No-op on non-Unix platforms.

	      Remove { path }
		     Delete a file or directory.

       All recipe paths are validated; absolute paths, .., empty paths, or . are rejected.  When force is false, existing files or directories	cause
       an error.

TYPES
       ArctgzConfig
	      Project configuration stored in arctgz.init.

	      name   Project name (alphanumeric, -, _; max 255 chars).

	      version
		     Semantic version string.

	      include
		     List of relative resource paths (max 100 entries, no .. or absolute paths).

	      compression
		     Compression algorithm: "gzip" (default) or "zstd".	 Determines archive format.

       ArctgzManifest Embedded in every archive as manifest.json.

	      name, version
		     Copied from config.

	      created
		     UTC timestamp of compilation.

	      compression
		     Algorithm used for this archive.

	      files  BTreeMap from archive paths to FileEntry.

       FileEntry Metadata for one file: size (u64) and sha512 hex string.

       ArctgzRecipe
	      Describes post-extraction actions.

	      name, version
		     Recipe identity.

	      steps  Ordered list of RecipeStep.

       RecipeStep
	      Enum with Copy, MkDir, Chmod, Remove.

       Compression
	      Enum: Gzip (default), Zstd.

       ArctgzError
	      All failure variants, now including:

	      RecipeNotFound
		     Recipe not found in archive.

	      RecipeInvalid
		     Recipe validation failed.

	      RecipeExecutionError
		     Recipe step could not be performed.

	      VerifyError
		     Verification failed (missing file, size mismatch, unsafe path, etc.).

EXAMPLE
   Initialising a project with zstd compression
       use arctgz::{init, load_config, save_config, Compression};

       fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
	   let project = Path::new("./my-project");
	   init(project, false)?;
	   let mut cfg = load_config(project)?;
	   cfg.compression = Compression::Zstd;
	   save_config(project, &cfg)?;
	   Ok(())
       }

   Compile, verify, and extract with a recipe
       use arctgz::{compile, verify, extract, execute_recipe, extract_recipe};

       fn build_and_deploy(project: &Path) -> Result<(), arctgz::ArctgzError> {
	   let archive = compile(project, None, false)?;
	   verify(&archive)?;
	   let out_dir = Path::new("/tmp/deploy");
	   extract(&archive, out_dir, true)?;
	   let recipe = extract_recipe(&archive)?;
	   execute_recipe(out_dir, &recipe, true)?;
	   Ok(())
       }

   Example recipe.json
       {
	 "name": "setup",
	 "version": "1.0.0",
	 "steps": [
	   { "action": "mkdir", "path": "logs" },
	   { "action": "copy", "from": "default.cfg", "to": "config.cfg" },
	   { "action": "chmod", "path": "bin/app", "mode": "755" },
	   { "action": "remove", "path": "temp.txt" }
	 ]
       }

FILES
       arctgz.init
	      Project configuration (JSON).  Now includes compression field.

       include/
	      Resource directory.

       dist/<name>-<version>.artgz
	      Default archive output (gzip or zstd).

       recipe.json (optional)
	      Post-extraction recipe embedded into the archive.

ENVIRONMENT
       HOME / USERPROFILE
	      Home directory for confinement checks (via dirs crate).

SECURITY
       • Home-directory confinement for init.

       • No side effects before validation.

       • Atomic writes (config, archive).

       • Archive integrity via SHA-512 manifest, verified on extract and verify.

       • Path traversal prevention in both extraction and recipe paths.

       • Symlink rejection during compilation.

       • Strict validation of all configuration and recipe inputs, including denial of unknown JSON fields.

VERSION
       arctgz  0.5.0 – adds zstd compression, parallel hashing, post-extraction recipes, standalone verification, and a unified compression detection
       layer.

SEE ALSO
       semver(7), realpath(3), serde_json(5), dirs(7), flate2(7), zstd(1), tar(5), sha2(7), rayon(7)

BUGS
       • The include/ directory is always empty initially; files must be added manually.

       • Concurrent operations on the same project directory are not serialised.

       • No cryptographic signatures yet; integrity relies solely on SHA-512 hashes.

       • Chmod step is silently ignored on non-Unix platforms.

